title: 'How to Get Away with Murder' 2.03 Preview: It Gets Frisky
text:
Comments When Annalise takes on a new client, the team must investigate a very high end sex club to get answers. 
Annalise Keating is teaching her class about the relation between sex and criminal law in the next episode of " How to Get Away with Murder ". She sends her interns to a very high end sex club to search for anything useful in her new case. Meanwhile, Annalise is still representing the siblings accused of killing their parents, but the case takes a turn for the worse when a new motive surfaces, and Wes teams up with an unexpected ally. Since there won't be a murder without a dead body, a preview for the next episode teases another casualty. There are also scenes that hint someone sneaks into Annalise's house and something scares her. "It's Called the Octopus" airs Thursday, October 8 at 10 P.M. on ABC.
